      <textAnnotation id="sid-070937E2-83A3-4383-8AC8-2718AB164C78" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Relabeling : Analyze Continuous improvement Plan</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-1A2C8AE2-4164-4E48-A817-8898AEDE34B0" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Dependency on below 2 L3s:
- Collect Supplier Performance Data
- Analyze Supplier Results</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-9EE09B84-CEBD-4640-A6A5-40093F2B3CDE" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Boundary apps (not S4 interface)
- Online supplier report card
- Supplier 360 (SAM, SDM)
- PowerBi dashboard
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-51B52AD8-F861-4D07-9E61-3B199BDAAB01" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>
L3 Process -
This is the process of reviewing a Supplier's performance against a mutually agreed-upon corrective action plan to identify those items that are exceeding meeting, or not meeting the action plan. Provide both qualitative and quantitative information and compare it against corrective action plan. Feedback should include part numbers, revisions, actions to be taken and by whom, stock purge data and dates of compliance, including any financial ownership as needed.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-68D98CEF-CFE4-4E5D-8A43-989FC9763887" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-040-210 Analyze Existing CAPs and Feedback to Suppliers</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-0E0E3016-F8ED-40D6-A766-346B967A620A" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Nageswaran, Rohan &lt;rohan.nageswaran@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
